TopicTitle: KSP Interstellar Extended Continued Development Thread

Articles.Content:
so solarwind for most of the stuff?

thanks for the information freethinker. i just stacked two MCF's one in DD mode. one in D-T mode, it was happiness... now im gonna rage at reactor embrittlement for a while, but the pittance of deuterium i put on the test craft (2400 approx) lasted 4 years, but only took 1 to reach embrittlement cap >< they dont makem like they used too!

18 minutes ago, Fairin said:

so solarwind for most of the stuff?

Solar wind contain a mixture of atoms emited by the sun, the majority consist of Hydrogen and Helium, only a fraction consists of Helium3

 

18 minutes ago, Fairin said:

 but the pittance of deuterium i put on the test craft (2400 approx) lasted 4 years, but only took 1 to reach embrittlement cap >< they dont makem like they used too!

Mm I see the problem. I have some ideas at least partialy  (based on skill level) revert the embrittlement, by allowing engeneers to repair the reactor on EVA  using rocket parts , at least that way you should be able to maintain the reactor for many ears at the expanse of labour cost and rocket parts. Would that be intresting? Note I'm planning a bigger role for Ketbal the engeneer anyway. It should also give you a reason to train your engeneers.

Edited August 9, 2016 by FreeThinker

i would probably build another fusion station and stick it up there (with the other) for 4 years then repair the 1 station 4 times to be honest

 

now if i got PAID to repair those stations...

or repairing gave a bonus i.e. embrittles 10% slower if repaired at 50%(max) embrittlement. Untill it doesnt embrittle anymore. That would motivate the hell out of me. would also make me create an engineer specific ship to go around and do that. 

or it could say be repaired 4 times, and it looses its embrittlement permanently would make me happier =P

Edited August 9, 2016 by Fairin
clarification.

3 hours ago, Fairin said:

i would probably build another fusion station and stick it up there (with the other) for 4 years then repair the 1 station 4 times to be honest

Why do you need constant power your Microwave network? Technically, you only need to power the network when you intend to use it, otherwise 99.9999999999% of your power is effectvely wasted.

Edited August 9, 2016 by FreeThinker

7 hours ago, FreeThinker said:

If you take a close look, you will notice the Research cost for reactor is significantly higher towards the end compaired to all other branches. I modified this intentional as this is the branch which unlocks the most powerfull reactors.

Well since tiers are assigned to specific time periods, then fission tech should be moved back to lower tier.

1 hour ago, raxo2222 said:

Well since tiers are assigned to specific time periods, then fission tech should be moved back to lower tier.

Well, that is not possible as that would make Nuclear reactors available before RTG. The problem is KSPI does not live in a vacuum, but has to adapt existing parts and part from other mods. Given I had only 6 tech nodes to work with, I think I did a pretty good job.

Edited August 9, 2016 by FreeThinker

also its a multiplayer server we all use the network abiet randomly, would be annoying to have someone cut it off while your landing, or have to turn it back on every time you make a ship.

I have a question.

What is everyone else using for fuel tanks for nuclear engine propellants? I find the Interstellar Liquid Fuel Tanks aren't quite varied enough to meet my needs... what I'd really like is the ability to put, say, hydrogen, into a Procedural Tank. Is there any way to do that?

Version 1.9.11 for Kerbal Space Program 1.1.3

Released on 2016-08-11

  • Added new part by Eleusis La Arwall: Microwave Rectenna , which comes available with Advanced Solar Technology and is now the only part able to Transmit Microwave Beamed Power
  • Lowered tech requirement Microwave Thermal Receiver to Advanced Solar Technology
  • Lowered tech requirement Microwave Dish Receiver to Advanced Solar Technology
  • Electric Thruster Maximum Power is affected by Wasteheat saturation.
  • Fixed Quantum Vacuum Thruster
  • Fixed Radiator compatibility with Near Future Electric technology

Greetings.

 

Is it just me, or is someone made a mistake on spelling again, my stock Ion Engine reads that it requires megajoules and Xenon Gas as fuel. All fueltanks, including those that comes with KSPI-E, reads XenonGas. I think that engines still work, but KER doesn't calculate their dV, which is bit of  a pain, really. I though that we rid from this weird resource naming thing, when pretty much all modders started to support CRP?

Well, I'll ask about one thing that is not implemented on KSPI, but maybe you can help me. I have picked up one engine from Near Future, and changed the propellant to NeonGas, just for fun. But I'm seeing that neon needs a cryostat tank, because when I reach big speeds on atmosphere, or when i make gross maneuvers on space, it consumes the NeonGas. Can anyone tell what I need to do? I've already done a tank that stores only neon.

6 hours ago, JohnWittle said:

I have a question.

What is everyone else using for fuel tanks for nuclear engine propellants? I find the Interstellar Liquid Fuel Tanks aren't quite varied enough to meet my needs... what I'd really like is the ability to put, say, hydrogen, into a Procedural Tank. Is there any way to do that? 

You can add every fuel to every fuel tank with Modular Fuel Tank. As far as I know is the only way to do it.

KSPI actually support CRP. It has CRP as a dependency and it's included in the download.

I know right. Here is the issue, someone who wrote the MM-patches for stock Ion engine and Nerteas engines, made a bloober of some sort. Also, while in the subject, who's smart idea was to make ion engines use MejaJoules instead of EC? Now tiny reactor wont able to power small ion probe, and that...isn't fun.

Liquid fuel,Oxidizer,LFO, monopropellant, diborane, kerosene, helium. In one of tanks HTP is missing.

Third one: Update MFT confing - its missing UF4/Kerosene/Diborane
